        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 91:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As with the individual, so with a nation: to stand in safety and be a witness to the destruction of the enemy is looked on as a sign of God’s favour.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord will be magnified . . . Israel.—Some render, let the Lord be magnified, as in Psalm 35:27; Psalm 40:16; others, the Lord is great: i.e., has exerted His greatness. The latter seems the more appropriate rendering here.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The Lord will be magnified . . . Israel.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Some render, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "let the Lord be magnified,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " as in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 35:27",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 40:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; others, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "the Lord is great: i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " has exerted His greatness. The latter seems the more appropriate rendering here.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "From the border.—Some say, beyond the border. This translation is not in accordance with the usage of the expression, which means simply “over” or “above.” (Comp. Jeremiah 4:6.) The meaning seems to be this: The Lord, whose protecting presence hovers specially over the border of Israel, is now great, in that He has restored Israel, but hath destroyed the nationality of the wicked descendants of the godless Esau. “Border of Israel” is purposely used in contrast to “border of wickedness.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "From the border.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Some say, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "beyond the border.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " This translation is not in accordance with the usage of the expression, which means simply “over” or “above.” (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 4:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) The meaning seems to be this: The Lord, whose protecting presence hovers specially over the border of Israel, is now great, in that He has restored Israel, but hath destroyed the nationality of the wicked descendants of the godless Esau. “Border of Israel” is purposely used in contrast to “border of wickedness.”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Malachi 1:6; Malachi 2:9.—The priesthood rebuked. A close connection subsists between the different parts of this section; it ought therefore to be read as one continuous paragraph. The sub-divisions of it are Malachi 1:6-14; Malachi 2:1-9.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Malachi 1:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Malachi 2:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".—The priesthood rebuked. A close connection subsists between the different parts of this section; it ought therefore to be read as one continuous paragraph. The sub-divisions of it are ",
            "children": []
          },
